            "answer_text": "Let\u2019s assuming it\u2019s a simple video call between two people. The average high definition video call uses approximately 1.5 Megabits per second (Mbps). According to Google\u2019s online calculator, you\u2019re consuming 675 MB an hour which is pretty close to a gigabyte.  Your actual numbers will vary depending on what app is used for video calling. One thing is for sure, video is a bandwidth intense application that consumes more data than a standard audio call. ",
